# AMC Task-Set Generation & Simulation — Claude Code Build Plan

Built to follow on from *Generating Utilization Vectors...* (DRS, RTSS 2020), *Analysis-Runtime
Co-design for Adaptive Mixed Criticality Scheduling* (RTAS 2022), and *Compensating Adaptive Mixed
Criticality Scheduling* (RTNS 2022).

## How to use this

1. Copy the three source PDFs into `docs/` in the new repo before starting — Claude Code can then
   cite exact equations/sections directly rather than relying on a paraphrase.
2. Paste the prompts below into Claude Code **one phase at a time**, in order. Each phase ends with
   a "Definition of done" — don't move to the next phase until that's satisfied (tests green, example
   output shown).
3. Phases 1–8 give you a complete, working pipeline for the baseline AMC scheme. Phase 9 is an
   optional extension that adds AMC-RH/AMC-RA as swappable scheduler variants, which lets you
   reproduce/extend the AMC-RH paper's comparison using your own N-sweep.
4. The numbers in the "Shared parameters" table are defaults, not requirements — adjust them in
   Prompt 3 before running the full sweep.

## Shared design decisions (review before starting)

| Decision | Default | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| HI/LO ratio | `Ci(HI) = 1.5 × Ci(LO)` per task (fixed ratio), **with a `--hi-mode` flag** to switch to DRS-independent control of total HI utilization | Fixed ratio is what you asked for; the independent mode avoids the correlation artefact the DRS paper flags in Baruah et al.'s original approach — worth comparing both |
| Failure probability | `FP = 1/N`, N swept over `{10, 100, 1000, 10000, 100000}` (log-spaced, configurable) | "1 in N jobs" as a range, per your request |
| Task set cardinality n | 20 | Paper convention |
| Criticality proportion CP | 0.5 | Paper convention |
| Utilization sweep U(LO) | 0.05 → 0.95, step 0.05 | Paper convention; generator should also report the analytic aggregate-feasibility ceiling for the current CP/CF (≈ 1/(CP·CF + (1−CP)); ≈0.8 for CP=0.5, CF=1.5) so you can see where task sets start becoming structurally infeasible |
| Replicates | 1000 per (U, N) combination | As requested |
| Simulation duration | 10⁶ ticks per run | As requested; engine is event-driven internally |
| Periods | log-uniform, ratio 100 (paper convention), integer ticks | Configurable; semi-harmonic left as a later option |
| Deadlines | `Di = Ti` (implicit) | Simplest starting point |
| BCET | uniform 80–100% of Ci(LO) | Paper convention; can be disabled (BCET=Ci(LO)) |
| Priority assignment | Deadline Monotonic | Optimal for implicit deadlines under single-criticality FPPS; Audsley OPA under AMC-rtb is a Phase 9 extension |
| Mode-change protocol | Original AMC (enter on Ci(LO) overrun, exit on idle instant) | Baseline from the AMC-RH paper; pluggable |
| Seeding | Deterministic seed derived from (U, N, hi_mode, replicate_index) | Full reproducibility |

