```
Implement amc_tasksim/analysis/plots.py, reading the results file from Phase 7.

Reproduce plots in the style of docs/AMCRRTAS2022.pdf Figures 1-3 (box-and-whisker: min,
5-percentile, 25-percentile/median/75-percentile box, 95-percentile, max) for NiD(%), TiD(%),
and JNE(%)+LDM(%), each as a function of U, faceted/coloured by N. Also produce:
- A heatmap of "Success Ratio" (fraction of task sets in each (U,N) cell with HDM=0, i.e. no
  high-criticality deadline misses — this should be ~100% everywhere if generation/analysis are
  correct, so a heatmap surfaces bugs quickly).
- A heatmap of the statistical-power diagnostic (total HI-trigger events per cell) so low-power
  regions are visually obvious.
- A comparison plot overlaying hi_mode="fixed_ratio" vs "drs_independent" results for the same
  (U, N) grid, on the JNE+LDM metric, to show the practical effect of the two generation
  strategies.

Save all figures to results/figures/. Provide a short markdown summary
(results/SUMMARY.md) written by you (Claude Code) after inspecting the actual output, describing
what the plots show and flagging anything that looks anomalous (e.g. non-zero HDM, low
statistical power regions, unexpectedly high individually-infeasible fractions under
fixed_ratio).
```

**Definition of done:** figures generated from the `--quick` run's output, `SUMMARY.md` written
and sensible.

